@startuml

title Session-Level Advisory Lock (Distributed Cron Worker)

participant "Worker A\n(cronWorker.js)" as WA
participant "Worker B\n(cronWorker.js)" as WB
participant "Lock Logic\n(locks.js)" as LOCKS
participant "pg Pool Client A\n(session)" as CLIENTA
participant "pg Pool Client B\n(session)" as CLIENTB
database "PostgreSQL" as PG
participant "Cron Runs Table\n(cron_runs)" as RUNS

== Periodic tick on both workers ==
WA -> LOCKS: runSingletonCronJob(worker-a)
WB -> LOCKS: runSingletonCronJob(worker-b)

LOCKS -> CLIENTA: pool.connect()
CLIENTA -> PG: SELECT pg_try_advisory_lock(CRON_SESSION_LOCK_KEY)
PG --> CLIENTA: true (lock acquired)
LOCKS -> RUNS: INSERT started row (worker-a)

LOCKS -> CLIENTB: pool.connect()
CLIENTB -> PG: SELECT pg_try_advisory_lock(CRON_SESSION_LOCK_KEY)
PG --> CLIENTB: false (another session holds lock)
CLIENTB --> LOCKS: release()
LOCKS --> WB: { locked: false, message: "skipped" }

LOCKS -> LOCKS: sleep(LONG_JOB_DURATION_MS)
LOCKS -> RUNS: UPDATE status = completed
CLIENTA -> PG: SELECT pg_advisory_unlock(CRON_SESSION_LOCK_KEY)
CLIENTA --> LOCKS: release()
LOCKS --> WA: { locked: true, runId }

note right of PG
Session advisory locks are held by the
database connection session. They must be
unlocked explicitly or released by closing
the connection.
end note

@enduml
